data.meta_description: Professional Boxer. Nicknamed The Manassa Mauler, he was Heavyweight Champion of the World from 1919 to 1926. The legendary Dempsey was born in Manassa, Colorado, one of 11 children. At 16 he left home and traveled on freight trains and fought to earn money.
